title.narrative: 603 STRENGTHENED FOR DECENTRALIZED PLANNING, IMPLEMENTATION AND MONITORING

description.narrative: Institutional capacities of governments at state level strengthened for decentralized planning, implementation, monitoring and using feedback in planning processes by 2022, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Reducing Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Social policies and strategies inform more effective and efficient planning, budgeting and implementation of social service programmes for reducing inequities and gender inequalities especially for the most vulnerable and marginalized children and adolescents by 2022

title.narrative: Institutional capacities of governments at state level strengthened for decentralized planning, implementation, monitoring andusing feedback in planning processes by 2022

description.narrative: Despite challenges related to COVID19 2nd wave response, improved coverage of social protection schemes in Maharashtra, Andhra Pradesh, Odisha, Jharkhand, Chhattisgarh and Uttar Pradesh, through UNICEF partnership with NGOs/CBOs to generate awareness among communities on government schemes. Working closely with the Gram Panchayats (GP) demonstrated scalable and replicable models, leading to strengthened institutional capacities of local governments (PRIs) for better outcomes for women and children in Assam, Maharashtra, Rajasthan, Odisha, Jharkhand, Karnataka, MP & Gujarat. All 16 state governments integrated child and gender responsive governance in PRI training curriculum and in GP (village) development plans and monitoring systems.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/01/2022
